@@ -1,3 +1,65 @@
 # libudev-freestanding
 
-Drop-in replacement for libudev without systemd
+Drop-in replacement for libudev without systemd.
+
+## Device configuration
+
+Devices are described by static config files under `/etc/udev/devices.d/`
+(override with the `UDEV_DEVICES_DIR` environment variable). Each file
+follows Linux's uevent format: `KEY=VALUE` lines, `#` for comments, blank
+lines ignored. Filenames are not significant â€” every regular file in the
+directory is parsed.
+
+### Recognized keys
+
+| Key            | Meaning                                                                              |
+| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
+| `NAME`         | **Required.** Device sysname (e.g. `card0`, `event0`, `i8042`).                      |
+| `SUBSYSTEM`    | **Required.** Subsystem name (e.g. `drm`, `input`, `platform`).                      |
+| `DEVNAME`      | **Absolute** path to the `/dev` node. `stat()`ed at load to learn the device number. |
+| `DEVTYPE`      | Device subtype (e.g. `drm_minor`, `partition`).                                      |
+| `DRIVER`       | Driver name.                                                                         |
+| `PARENT`       | Parent device, as `<name>` (same subsystem) or `<subsystem>/<name>`.                 |
+| `ATTR{name}=v` | A sysattr value (udev-rule syntax). Repeatable. Read-only at runtime.                |
+
+The syspath is synthesised as `/sys/devices/<SUBSYSTEM>/<NAME>`. Filenames
+in the config dir have no semantic meaning.
+
+Any other `KEY=VALUE` line becomes a plain device property exposed via
+`udev_device_get_property_value()` and the property iterator.
+
+### Example
+
+`/etc/udev/devices.d/card0`:
+
+```
+NAME=card0
+SUBSYSTEM=drm
+DEVNAME=/dev/drm/card0
+DEVTYPE=drm_minor
+```
+
+`/etc/udev/devices.d/event0`:
+
+```
+NAME=event0
+SUBSYSTEM=input
+DEVNAME=/dev/input/event0
+PARENT=platform/i8042
+ID_INPUT=1
+ID_INPUT_KEYBOARD=1
+ATTR{name}=AT Translated Set 2 keyboard
+```
+
+## Limitations
+
+The build is config-driven only; there are no runtime probes of `/sys`.
+The following APIs are stubbed:
+
+- `udev_monitor_*` returns a real, never-readable pipe fd; no events ever
+  arrive. `udev_monitor_receive_device()` always returns `NULL` with `errno`
+  set to `EAGAIN`.
+- `udev_queue_*` always reports an empty, idle queue.
+- `udev_hwdb_*` lookups always return an empty result.
+- `udev_device_set_sysattr_value()` returns `-EROFS`; the registry is
+  read-only.
